1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,572
Management is stratified by disease severity.

2
00:00:02,572 --> 00:00:05,573
For hemodynamically stable patients, standard heart failure

3
00:00:05,573 --> 00:00:08,574
therapy — ACE inhibitors, beta-blockers, and diuretics

4
00:00:08,574 --> 00:00:10,289
— is the cornerstone.

5
00:00:10,289 --> 00:00:13,290
Competitive athletic activity must be restricted for

6
00:00:13,290 --> 00:00:16,290
a minimum of 3 to 6 months,

7
00:00:16,290 --> 00:00:19,291
given the risk of arrhythmic death during

8
00:00:19,291 --> 00:00:20,149
myocardial inflammation.

9
00:00:20,149 --> 00:00:23,150
In fulminant myocarditis with cardiogenic shock, early

10
00:00:23,150 --> 00:00:26,150
mechanical circulatory support — intra-aortic balloon pump,

11
00:00:26,150 --> 00:00:29,151
Impella, or veno-arterial ECMO — is critical

12
00:00:29,151 --> 00:00:32,152
and has been shown to bridge patients

13
00:00:32,152 --> 00:00:33,010
to recovery.

14
00:00:33,010 --> 00:00:36,010
Immunosuppressive therapy with corticosteroids is indicated for

15
00:00:36,010 --> 00:00:38,583
giant cell myocarditis and cardiac sarcoidosis.

16
00:00:38,583 --> 00:00:41,583
IVIG may be considered in viral etiologies

17
00:00:41,583 --> 00:00:42,870
in pediatric patients.

18
00:00:42,870 --> 00:00:45,870
ICD implantation should be deferred until myocardial

19
00:00:45,870 --> 00:00:48,871
recovery is assessed at 3 to 6

20
00:00:48,871 --> 00:00:49,300
months.
